13. January 1643. Fo. 85. Both Houſes diſtinctly, make great acknowledgement to the City, with aſſurance never to diſſert it;
but to make it their greateſt care, to watch all opportunitys to advance the honour and happineſs of the City, which under God hath
been the principal means of preſerving the Parliament.
